<b>OBJECTIVE</b>

</br>Nevo is looking for proven Senior Sales Executive to grow our <b><u>Enterprise Application Integration (EAI) practice</u></b>. The Senior Sales Executive will strategize, develop and execute a sales plan to meet company's revenue objectives for the <b><u>EAI practice</u></b>, building a pipeline, working closely with Nevo’s technical staff to qualify and close, and then seeing projects through to conclusion. This position is instrumental in helping Nevo meet its revenue and profitability goals. This is a high profile growth opportunity that demands a technically oriented, highly motivated individual with strong sales, communications and organizational skills that is eager to learn and become part of a growing custom software solutions company. Nevo compensates high performance with substantial upside potential.
</br>


<b>MAJOR DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</b>

<ul class="tightBodyText">

     <li>Identify software consulting and development opportunities for <b><u>Enterprise
Application Integration</u></b> engagements. This includes cold calling and prospecting,
responding to existing client sales needs, and efficiently closing sales opportunities.

</li><li>Develop opportunities into qualified prospects for Nevo's services.

</li><li>Develop sales proposals and work with Nevo staff on proposal development efforts.

</li><li>Negotiate and close new business.

</li><li>Work with prospects to determine client needs and assist in formulating IT-based alternatives and solutions.

</li><li>Plan, direct and control own resources, activities, and costs, to ensure effective sales performance.

</li><li>Develop key relationships with prospects and clients to develop new sales and grow revenues in existing accounts.

</li><li>Effectively represent corporate capabilities to prospects.

</li><li>Work effectively with Nevo project managers, architects, and implementation teams in presales situations and in successfully setting projects in motion.

</li><li>Develop and pursue a sales plan consistent with Nevo's corporate strategy.

</li><li>Maintain sales plan and periodically update sales forecasts and pipeline.

</li><li>Communicate effectively with the Nevo management team regarding the sales plan, pipeline, and anticipated project support requirements.

</li>

</ul>

<b>ESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS</b>

<ul class="tightBodyText">


<li>Bring a portfolio of New England EAI contacts and prospects that would be strong candidates for Nevo's EAI professional services practice
</li><li>Track record of success: 5+ years successful experience in sales executive roles, 3+ years selling integration solutions, consistently achieving targets
</li><li>Solid experience selling EAI professional services engagements to mid- and large-sized companies
</li><li>Proven ability to work at all levels of a client organization (CxO, IT management, LOB Management)
</li><li>Demonstrated ability to build contacts and gain access to integration projects
</li><li>Strong intuitive sales skills&#8212;able to establish and build confidence and trust
</li><li>Excellent written and oral communication skills
</li><li>Experience with solution selling / consultative selling approaches
</li><li>Sales or related work experience in the industry or in a related business
</li><li>BS in a related field or equivalent needed
</li>
</ul>

